%
% ISO 32000-2
%   ColorDodge: 0                  if cb = 0
%               1                  if cb >= 1 - cs
%               cb/(1 - cs)        otherwise
%
% NOTE 10 Brightens the backdrop colour to reflect the source colour. Painting with
% black produces no change.
%
% NOTE 11 This function is formulated in a different way here than it is in ISO 32000-1:2008.
% However, it produces the same results except in one special edge case. For ColorDodge, 
% the special case is cb = 0 and cs = 1, where the result is now 0 instead of 1. The rationale
% for the change is that for any given cb, the result should be a continuous function of cs.
%
% cb = 1 when RGB is full intensity. 
% cs = 0 is white for RGB.
%

